      "source": "inferred"
    },
    "output_variable": "invoices_missing_invoice_number"
  },
  {
    "id": "step9",
    "name": "Generate an HTML email body with a per-invoice table, roll-up totals, and exceptions list",
    "type": "ai_processing",
    "input": "{{extracted_invoices}}",
    "config": {
      "type": "generate",
      "input": "{{extracted_invoices}}",
      "ai_type": "generate",
      "instruction": "Generate a professional HTML email body for an invoice summary. Structure:\n\n1. HEADER: Include a short greeting, the Google Drive folder link (from config folder_link), and the total number of invoices found (from total_invoice_count).\n\n2. IF total_invoice_count is 0: State that no invoices were found in the folder and include the folder link. Skip the table and totals.\n\n3. IF invoices exist: Create an HTML <table> with styled borders, header row with background color, and padding. Columns: File Name, Vendor, Invoice #, Invoice Date, Due Date, Total, Currency, Notes. One row per invoice from extracted_invoices. For any missing field, leave the cell blank and add a note in the Notes column (e.g., 'Missing invoice number', 'Missing total amount'). Format dates consistently (YYYY-MM-DD). Format amounts with 2 decimal places.\n\n4. TOTALS SECTION: Show total number of invoices, sum of all totals (from sum_of_totals) with a note if some invoices had no total. List exceptions: invoices missing totals (from invoices_missing_total — list their file names) and invoices missing invoice numbers (from invoices_missing_invoice_number — list their file names).\n\n5. Use clean, professional HTML styling suitable for email clients.",
      "output_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "subject",
          "body"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "body": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Complete HTML email body with table and totals"
          },
          "subject": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Email subject line"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "prompt": "Generate a professional HTML email body for an invoice summary. Structure:\n\n1. HEADER: Include a short greeting, the Google Drive folder link (from config folder_link), and the total number of invoices found (from total_invoice_count).\n\n2. IF total_invoice_count is 0: State that no invoices were found in the folder and include the folder link. Skip the table and totals.\n\n3. IF invoices exist: Create an HTML <table> with styled borders, header row with background color, and padding. Columns: File Name, Vendor, Invoice #, Invoice Date, Due Date, Total, Currency, Notes. One row per invoice from extracted_invoices. For any missing field, leave the cell blank and add a note in the Notes column (e.g., 'Missing invoice number', 'Missing total amount'). Format dates consistently (YYYY-MM-DD). Format amounts with 2 decimal places.\n\n4. TOTALS SECTION: Show total number of invoices, sum of all totals (from sum_of_totals) with a note if some invoices had no total. List exceptions: invoices missing totals (from invoices_missing_total — list their file names) and invoices missing invoice numbers (from invoices_missing_invoice_number — list their file names).\n\n5. Use clean, professional HTML styling suitable for email clients.",
    "step_id": "step9",
    "description": "Generate an HTML email body with a per-invoice table, roll-up totals, and exceptions list",
    "input_schema": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
